ipate%20heat.%20Materials%20like%20Avcoat%20(used%20in%20Apollo%20missions%20and%20the%20Orion%20Crew%20Capsule)%20and%20Phenolic-Impregnated%20Carbon%20Ablator%20(PICA)%20help%20prevent%20overheating.%20SpaceX%20even%20developed%20its%20own%20version%2C%20PICA-X%2C%20for%20the%20Dragon%20capsule.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EArc%20Jet%20Testing%20-%20At%20Ames'%20Arc%20Jet%20Complex%2C%20NASA%20scientists%20recreate%20the%20scorching%20heat%20of%20atmospheric%20entry%2C%20subjecting%20heat%20shields%20to%20plasma%20hotter%20than%20the%20Sun's%20surface.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EComputer%20Simulations%20-%20Supercomputers%20model%20reentry%20dynamics%20to%20predict%20and%20solve%20technical%20challenges%20before%20missions%20launch.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EADEPT%20and%20HEEET%20-%20New%20materials%20and%20deployable%20heat%20shields%2C%20like%20HEEET%20(Heatshield%20for%20Extreme%20Entry%20Environment%20Technology)%20and%20ADEPT%20(Adaptable%2C%20Deployable%20Entry%20Placement%20Technology)%2C%20aim%20to%20enhance%20spacecraft%20protection%20for%20missions%20to%20Mars%2C%20Venus%2C%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ELessons%20from%20Past%20Missions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20has%20learned%20invaluable%20lessons%20from%20past%20missions%2C%20from%20the%20Apollo%20moon%20missions%20to%20the%20Mars%20Science%20Laboratory%20and%20Stardust%20comet%20sample%20return%20mission.%20Even%20the%20Space%20Shuttle%20programme%2C%20which%20featured%20reusable%20orbiters%2C%20provided%20valuable%20insights%20into%20reentry%20aerodynamics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Apollo%2C%20Challenger%2C%20Columbia%20Lessons%20Learned%20Programme%20(ACCLLP)%2C%20established%20in%202016%2C%20ensures%20that%20insights%20from%20critical%20missions%20are%20shared%20across%20generations%20to%20prevent%20past%20failures%20from%20repeating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Apollo%2013%20mission%2C%20famously%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bsuccessful%20failure%2C%26quot%3B%20demonstrated%20the%20importance%20of%20contingency%20planning%20and%20problem-solving%20when%20an%20oxygen%20tank%20explosion%20jeopardised%20the%20crew's%20survival.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA's%20Lessons%20Learned%20Information%20System%20(LLIS)%20supports%20knowledge-sharing%2C%20allowing%20engineers%20to%20make%20informed%20decisions%20and%20mitigate%20risks%20in%20future%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ENASA's%20Space%20Shuttle%20Programme%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Freference%2Fthe-space-shuttle%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA's%20Space%20Shuttle%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20ran%20from%201981%20to%202011%2C%20was%20the%20first%20to%20use%20reusable%20spacecraft%20for%20human%20spaceflight.%20The%20fleet%20included%20Columbia%2C%20Challenger%2C%20Discovery%2C%20Atlantis%2C%20and%20Endeavour%2C%20designed%20to%20carry%20up%20to%20seven%20astronauts%20and%20various%20payloads%20into%20low%20Earth%20orbit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Shuttle%20launched%20like%20a%20rocket%2C%20operated%20in%20space%2C%20and%20returned%20to%20Earth%20like%20a%20glider.%20It%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20deploying%20satellites%2C%20conducting%20scientific%20experiments%2C%20repairing%20the%20Hubble%20Space%20Telescope%2C%20and%20assembling%20the%20ISS.%20The%20program%20completed%20135%20missions%20but%20faced%20major%20tragedies%20-%20the%20Challenger%20disaster%20in%201986%20and%20Columbia%20in%202003%20-%20leading%20to%20critical%20safety%20improvements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Shuttle%20consisted%20of%20an%20orbiter%20vehicle%2C%20two%20solid%20rocket%20boosters%2C%20and%20an%20external%20fuel%20tank%2C%20with%20all%20components%20except%20the%20tank%20being%20reusable.%20After%20the%20programme%20ended%20in%202011%2C%20NASA%20shifted%20focus%20to%20new%20spaceflight%20technologies%20and%20partnerships%2C%20using%20lessons%20from%20the%20Shuttle%20era%20to%20develop%20future%20exploration%20missions%2C%20including%20Artemis%20and%20commercial%20crew%20programmes.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742298600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fpji00vpo_sunita-williams_625x300_17_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-sunita-williams-will-experience-during-spacecraft-reentry-to-earth-7950013%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20the%20astronaut's%20perspective%2C%20the%20view%20from%20a%20window%20during%20reentry%20is%20nothing%20but%20a%20wall%20of%20fire.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-sunita-williams-will-experience-during-spacecraft-reentry-to-earth-7950013%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gippy%20Grewal%20DEFENDS%20Ibrahim%20starrer%20Nadaaniyan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742298517000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119161855%2Cimgsize-43676.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fgippy-grewal-defends-ibrahim-ali-khan-khushi-kapoor-amid-backlash-over-their-performance-in-nadaaniyan-when-saif-ali-khans-first-film-released-%2Farticleshow%2F119161855.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F119161855.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EGippy%20Grewal%2C%20at%20Akaal's%20trailer%20launch%2C%20addressed%20the%20backlash%20against%20Ibrahim%20Ali%20Khan%20and%20Khushi%20Kapoor's%20debut%20in%20Nadaaniyan.%20Recalling%20his%20own%20initial%20criticism%20during%20Carry%20On%20Jatta%2C%20he%20emphasized%20that%20such%20feedback%20can%20be%20a%20driving%20force.%20Karan%20Johar%20supported%20moving%20forward%20despite%20opinions.%20Nadaaniyan%20premiere