's%20my%20advice%20for%20federal%20workers%20making%20the%20switch.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22First%20Lady%20Michelle%20Obama%20greets%20Hannah%20August%20in%20the%20Blue%20Room%20of%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Dec.%206%2C%202013.%20(Official%20White%20House%20Photo%20by%20Chuck%20Kennedy)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d8208db8b41a9673fad1a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFirst%20Lady%20Michelle%20Obama%20greets%20Hannah%20August%20in%20the%20Blue%20Room%20of%20the%20White%20House.%3Cp%3EChuck%20Kennedy%2FThe%20White%20House%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHannah%20August%20started%20her%20career%20in%202006%20working%20up%20the%20ranks%20in%20the%20Senate%20press%20office.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20worked%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20and%20as%20press%20secretary%20to%20former%20First%20Lady%20Michelle%20Obama.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAugust%20left%20her%20job%20in%20the%20White%20House%20for%20better%20work-life%20balance%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Hannah%20August%2C%20a%20communications%20consultant%20and%20former%20White%20House%20employee.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20verified%20her%20employment%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20got%20my%20first%20job%20in%202006%20working%20up%20the%20ranks%20in%20the%20US%20Senate%20press%20office.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20mentor%20hired%20me%20as%20his%20deputy%20at%20the%20Democratic%20Senatorial%20Campaign%20Committee%2C%20and%20then%20I%20was%20hired%20as%20the%20press%20secretary%20for%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20Obama%20administration.%20While%20there%2C%20I%20collaborated%20with%20the%20White%20House%2C%20which%20later%20recruited%20me%20as%20the%20President's%20regional%20communications%20director%20in%202010.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20six%20months%2C%20I%20became%20the%20First%20Lady's%20press%20secretary.%20I'd%20studied%20international%20relations%2C%20but%20most%20of%20my%20experience%20came%20from%20learning%20on%20the%20job%20from%20mentors.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20work%20with%20President%20Obama%20focused%20on%20economics.%20Working%20for%20the%20First%20Lady%2C%20I%20engaged%20more%20with%20consumer-focused%20media%2C%20like%20TV%20shows%2C%20magazines%2C%20and%20children's%20programming.%20My%20main%20remit%20was%20%26quot%3BLet's%20Move%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20initiative%20tackling%20obesity%2C%20as%20well%20as%20events%20at%20the%20White%20House%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Easter%20Egg%20Roll%2C%20state%20dinners%2C%20and%20music%20events.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22db06b07b-dc2a-4944-8e63-90a484c5896f%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ELong%20hours%20and%20high%20pressure%20burned%20me%20out%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20government%20is%20working%20well%2C%20which%20I%20think%20it%20often%20does%2C%20federal%20workers%20can%20see%20their%20contributions%20are%20directly%20impacting%20people.%20I%20enjoyed%20making%20positive%20changes%20and%20every%20day%20was%20different.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20said%2C%20the%20hours%20were%20long%2C%20and%20the%20stress%20levels%20were%20high.%20The%20biggest%20stress%20was%20a%20feeling%20of%20needing%20to%20be%20perfect%20because%20any%20mistake%20would%20be%20amplified.%20Having%20a%20huge%20spotlight%20on%20everything%20I%20did%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure.%20I%20was%20on%20a%20plane%20at%20least%20once%20a%20week%2C%20and%20it%20was%20crazy%20busy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20five%20years%20in%20the%20administration%2C%20including%20nearly%20three%20with%20the%20First%20Lady%2C%20the%20payoff%20stopped%20feeling%20worth%20it.%20I%20was%20burned%20out%20and%20tired.%20I%20wanted%20better%20work-life%20balance%20and%20less%20pressure.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20were%20White%20House%20lifers%2C%20but%20plenty%20of%20people%20left%20the%20administration%20after%20a%20couple%20of%20terms%20to%20go%20into%20the%20private%20sector.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224ea1b59d-e129-4593-8eec-96367582cea9%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20considered%20a%20total%20pivot%2C%20but%20the%202016%20election%20refocused%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere's%20no%20singular%20approach%20to%20making%20the%20switch.%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20specific%20job%20in%20mind%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20meaningful%20work%2C%20balance%2C%20and%20to%20stay%20in%20D.C.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20cast%20a%20wide%20net%2C%20met%20with%20many%20people%2C%20and%20had%20countless%20coffees.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20role%20at%20National%20Geographic%20Kids%20came%20from%20a%20past%20collaboration%20%E2%80%94%20while%20at%20the%20White%20House%2C%20I%20helped%20organize%20a%20Guinness%20World%20Record%20attempt%20with%20them.%20It%20was%20for%20the%20most%20people%20doing%20jumping%20jacks.%20When%20they%20were%20crafting%20a%20lead%20marketing%20role%20for%20kids%20and%20family%20products%2C%20my%20experience%20made%20me%20a%20natural%20fit.%20There%20was%20no%20job%20posting%2C%20but%20conversations%20led%20to%20interviews%20and%20the%20role.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI'd%20always%20wanted%20to%20work%20at%20National%20Geographic%2C%20but%20after%20two%20years%2C%20I%20realized%20the%20culture%20was%20too%20slow.%20I%20took%20a%20year%20to%20explore%20my%20passions%20%E2%80%94%20studying%20interior%20design%2C%20directing%20a%20play%2C%20shadowing%20a%20real%20estate%20developer%2C%20and%20training%20my%20dog%20as%20a%20therapy%20dog.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20considering%20a%20total%20career%20shift%2C%20but%20Trump's%202016%20election%20refocused%20me%20on%20using%20my%20skills%20for%20good.%20I%20became%20director%20of%20communications%20at%20an%20NGO%20for%20global%20gender%20equality%2C%20and%20two%20years%20later%2C%20I%20founded%20my%20communications%20firm%2C%20Jellyfish%20Strategies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d905d257-d0ba-4a84-aa39-f44ca93524e3%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20missed%20the%20energy%20and%20life%20of%20government%2C%20but%20you%20couldn't%20pay%20me%20to%20go%20back%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20switched%20to%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20there%20was%20often%20more%20bureaucracy%20than%20in%20government.%20There's%20sometimes%20a%20misconception%20of%20government%20as%20a%20place%20where%20nothing%20gets%20done%2C%20with%20millions%20of%20files%20and%20forms%20to%20make%20anything%20move.%20There's%20always%20room%20for%20improvement%2C%20but%20from%20my%20experience%2C%20it%20was%20effective%20and%20smooth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20one%20in%20government%20does%20it%20for%20the%20money.%20Overall%2C%20my%20salary%20has%20increased%20since%20leaving%20government%20work.%20I%20was%20also%20surprised%20that%20even%20though%20I%20left%20the%20government%20for%20a%20better%20work-life%20balance%2C%20I%20missed%20the%20energy%20of%20politics.%20I%20still%20find%20working%20with%20my%20clients%20exciting%2C%20but%20I'm%20just%20working%20with%20a%20different%20vibe%20in%20general.%20I%20have%20a%20six-year-old.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22da4151e5-4910-4d09-b946-3928b5b9d2fa%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20advice%20to%20federal%20workers%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20a%20tough%20time%20for%20folks%20who%20have%20been%20cut%20adrift%20from%20their%20federal%20roles.%20Being%20pushed%20out%20is%20disheartening%2C%20but%20know%20that%20many%20appreciate%20your%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20the%20way%20I%20viewed%20and%20narrativized%20my%20move%20out%20for%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Mrs.%20Obama%20gave%20me%20great%20career%20advice%3A%20at%20different%20life%20stages%2C%20you'll%20need%20different%20things%20%E2%80%94%20challenge%2C%20stability%2C%20balance%2C%20or%20money.%20Sometimes%2C%20just%20focus%20on%20the%20next%20job%20and%20go%20from%20there.%20Your%20needs%20will%20evolve%2C%20so%20stay%20open%20to%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20mentor%2C%20Maria%20Cristina%20%26quot%3BMC%26quot%3B%20Gonz%C3%A1lez%20Noguera%2C%20worked%20at%20Estee%20Lauder%20before%20joining%20the%20First%20Lady's%20team.%20She%20had%20to%20learn%20how%20her%20skills%20applied%20to%20government.%20She%20told%20me%20that%20many%20of%20the%20skills%20I%20had%20developed%20were%20transferable%20to%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20but%20the%20people%20hiring%20me%20may%20not%20see%20that%20instantly.%20You%20really%20have%20to%20spell%20it%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20example%2C%20managing%20%26quot%3Bexecutive%20communications%26quot%3B%20wasn't%20a%20term%20I%20used%20in%20the%20government%2C%20but%20that%20was%20part%20of%20my%20role%20for%20the%20Attorney%20General%20and%20First%20Lady.%20MC%20helped%20me%20tweak%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20match%20corporate%20language.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENetworking%20is%20invaluable%2C%20both%20with%20people%20you%20know%20directly%20and%20mutual%20connections.%20There%20were%20lists%20of%20Obama%20alumni%2C%20and%20I%20imagine%20now%20networks%20are%20being%20set%20up%20for%20federal%20workers%20who%20are%20out%20of%20a%20job.%20Be%20sure%20to%20follow%20up%20strategically%20%E2%80%94%20don't%20hound%20people%2C%20but%20check%20in%20occasionally%20to%20stay%20on%20their%20radar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBe%20open%20to%20geography%20moves.%20There%20are%20lots%20of%20people%20in%20D.C.%20suddenly%20out%20of%20a%20government%20job%2C%20and%20not%20enough%20industry%20to%20absorb%20them.%20Definitely%20explore%20potential%20moves%20to%20other%20places%20if%20you%20can.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20the%20private%20sector%20isn't%20for%20you%2C%20consider%20local%20government%20work%2C%20which%20can%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20good%20and%20help%20you%20continue%20giving%20back%20to%20the%20country.%20I%20hope%20that%20lots%20of%20people%20do%20consider%20that%20shift.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-worker-moved-private-sector-advice-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742292286000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d820c1585f1dff88b24fc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-worker-moved-private-sector-advice-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20working%20in%20government%20for%20years%2C%20including%20as%20press%20secretary%20to%20the%20former%20First%20Lady%2C%20Hannah%20August%20pivoted%20to%20private%20sector%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Megan%20Carnegie)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-worker-moved-private-sector-advice-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pilgrim%20secures%20Rs%20200%20cr%20in%20funding%20at%20Rs%203%2C000%20cr%20pre-money%20valuation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742292212000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fpilgrim-secures-rs-200-cr-in-funding-at-rs-3-000-cr-pre-money-valuation-125031800690_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20beauty%20brand%20will%