%20of%20mid-March%2C%20law%20school%20applications%20were%20up%2020%25%20from%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20figures%20from%20the%20Law%20School%20Admission%20Council%20show.%20More%20than%20200%20law%20programs%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%20make%20up%20the%20nonprofit's%20membership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaw%20school%20admissions%20sometimes%20move%20in%20a%20pendulum%20%E2%80%94%20up%20one%20year%2C%20down%20the%20next%2C%20said%20Mike%20Spivey%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20Spivey%20Consulting%20Group%2C%20which%20offers%20services%20to%20help%20people%20through%20the%20application%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20there%20have%20been%20two%20years%20in%20a%20row%20of%20sharp%20increases%20in%20applications.%20He%20credits%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-hard-to-find-job-us-though-unemployment-low-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esluggish%20corporate%20hiring%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20presidential%20election%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0candidates%20are%20often%20lawyers%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20the%20daily%20prominence%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-workers-tough-job-search-private-sector-roles-layoffs-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20fights%20in%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20I%20would%20call%20three%20atmospheric%20pressures%20on%20steroids%2C%26quot%3B%20Spivey%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20back-to-back%20increases%20in%20applications%20are%20rare%2C%20he%20said.%20It%20happened%20after%20the%209%2F11%20terrorist%20attacks%20and%20after%20the%20Great%20Recession%20of%202007%20to%202009%2C%20Spivey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20through%20what%20could%20be%20a%20tougher%20admissions%20process%2C%20here%20are%20some%20key%20things%20to%20remember%2C%20admissions%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e187f380-4d56-4284-881c-054682106be4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStay%20positive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpivey%20said%20it's%20important%20that%20people%20stay%20%26quot%3Bebullient%26quot%3B%20if%20they%20can%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20give%20up%20too%20soon%20%E2%80%94%20because%20the%20application%20process%20can%20be%20drawn%20out.%20He%20said%20it's%20fair%20to%20let%20a%20program%20know%20when%20it's%20your%20dream%20school%20and%20that%2C%20if%20admitted%2C%20you%20would%20attend%20without%20hesitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20type%20of%20messaging%20during%20a%20long%2C%20slow%20summer%20%26quot%3Breally%20tends%20to%20pay%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Spivey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it's%20more%20sensible%20than%20giving%20up%20too%20early%20and%20planning%20to%20apply%20the%20following%20year%20because%20it's%20not%20certain%20applications%20will%20drop.%20At%20his%20firm%2C%20inquiries%20are%20already%20up%2020%25%20from%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20Spivey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22046f908e-9ced-4502-b1c4-5787a68b29b6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBe%20patient%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKyle%20McEntee%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20prelaw%20engagement%20at%20the%20Law%20School%20Admission%20Council%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20because%20applications%20are%20up%2C%20admissions%20teams%20are%20busy.%20Many%20are%20also%20trying%20to%20ensure%20they%20get%20the%20right%20balance%20and%20avoid%20enrolling%20too%20many%20students.%20That%20can%20slow%20the%20process%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20applied%20and%20are%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20strengthen%20your%20application%2C%20McEntee%20said%20one%20step%20could%20be%20to%20contact%20your%20undergraduate%20prelaw%20advisor%2C%20even%20if%20you've%20already%20graduated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20advisor%20might%20be%20able%20to%20contact%20the%20admissions%20department%20on%20your%20behalf%20to%20ask%20for%20advice%20on%20how%20someone%20might%20bolster%20their%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223cc7734f-fdb7-4d58-8819-f4b1683f9005%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKeep%20communications%20professional%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMcEntee%20said%20that%20communications%20with%20law%20schools%20should%20always%20be%20professional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20using%20big%20words%2C%20however.%20Instead%2C%20it%20means%20responding%20promptly%20and%20giving%20thorough%20answers%20to%20questions%20you%20might%20get%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApplicants%20%26quot%3Bneed%20to%20look%20at%20every%20communication%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20impress%2C%26quot%3B%20McEntee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283ac4f55-35ab-4c62-a6e3-bd0bcd9e2c1d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStay%20in%20contact%20with%20admissions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpivey%20said%20it's%20reasonable%20to%20ping%20the%20admissions%20office%20every%20six%20weeks%20to%20reiterate%20your%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSchools%20love%20hearing%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20not%20good%2C%20Spivey%20said%2C%20is%20to%20contact%20a%20school%20to%20calm%20your%20nerves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20you'd%20ideally%20want%20to%20reach%20out%20if%20something%20has%20changed%20that%20could%20make%20you%20look%20more%20attractive%20to%20admissions%20departments.%20That%20might%20be%20a%20bump%20up%20in%20your%20GPA%2C%20a%20higher%20LSAT%20score%2C%20or%20landing%20a%20solid%20summer%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnything%20that%20makes%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20stronger%20are%20great%20ways%20to%20organically%20get%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20law%20school%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20McEntee%20said%20applicants%20should%20avoid%20pushing%20too%20hard%20or%20overdoing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20stand%20out%20for%20the%20wrong%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcEntee%20said%20that%20because%20every%20school%20has%20different%20procedures%2C%20constraints%2C%20and%20expectations%2C%20it's%20smart%20to%20ask%20them%20what%20they%20might%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20law%20school%20wants%20to%20be%20just%20inundated%20with%20unsolicited%20materials%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228665e3e4-a16f-4756-a3b3-c273be913bbd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKeep%20trying%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpivey%20said%20nearly%20every%20school%20tends%20to%20have%20one%20or%20two%20enrolled%20students%20who%20don't%20show%20up%20for%20orientation.%20That%20could%20be%20a%20last-minute%20route%20in%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%20higher%20score%20and%20it's%20on%20track%20with%20the%20program's%20median%20levels%2C%20and%20you've%20been%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20program%20periodically%20during%20the%20summer%20in%20an%20upbeat%20way%2C%20the%20school%20may%20say%20yes%2C%20Spivey%20said.%20In%20part%2C%20that's%20to%20avoid%20the%20lost%20tuition%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20aspiring%20law%20students%20can%20also%20retake%20the%20LSAT%20to%20try%20to%20improve%20their%20scores.%20There%20is%20a%20test%20in%20June%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20never%20too%20late%20to%20get%20a%20higher%20score%2C%26quot%3B%20Spivey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaw-school-applications-surge-economic-worry-slow-hiring-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742289181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d88cf969253ccddf997f4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaw-school-applications-surge-economic-worry-slow-hiring-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Law%20school%20applications%20are%20up%2020%25%20from%20a%20year%20ago%20amid%20economic%20and%20political%20pressures.%20Here%20is%20some%20key%20advice%20for%20the%20tougher%20environment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%